  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study evaluates, if the movement of the cervical spine, assessed via a specific
      questionnaire by the patient, is a valid and reliable tool and could be used in daily
      clinical routine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Cervical range of motion is a frequently used assessment methods in patients with neck pain.

      Although it seems to be used frequently, clinicians still prefer hands-on assessment.
      Furthermore it is interesting, if cervical range of motion,self-assessed by the patient is a
      valid and reliable tool.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
